1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:01,386
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,387 --> 00:00:02,954
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:03,170 --> 00:00:05,564
(30 years ago)

4
00:00:06,852 --> 00:00:09,452
(Episode 3)

5
00:00:18,591 --> 00:00:21,097
Seung Hyun!

6
00:00:24,060 --> 00:00:25,870
- Your cello aunt is here!
- Aunt!

7
00:00:25,895 --> 00:00:28,626
Your cello aunt is here!

8
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:31,124
- Where's your dad?
- You're here?

9
00:00:35,206 --> 00:00:37,547
- Congratulations on your son.
- Thank you.

10
00:00:37,631 --> 00:00:38,787
How's Yeong Ju?

11
00:00:39,043 --> 00:00:40,503
- Go on in.
- Okay.

12
00:00:41,443 --> 00:00:43,530
I'll go see the baby.

13
00:00:49,742 --> 00:00:52,109
- Yeong Ju!
- Your cello aunt is here!

14
00:00:57,378 --> 00:00:58,590
Congratulations.

15
00:00:58,614 --> 00:01:00,010
Thank you.

16
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:01,930
Seung Woo, say hello to your aunt.

17
00:01:01,963 --> 00:01:03,516
Say, "Hello, Aunt."

18
00:01:03,540 --> 00:01:04,931
Who do you take after?

19
00:01:04,956 --> 00:01:07,375
I think you look like your mom.

20
00:01:08,763 --> 00:01:11,201
You're so lucky. I'm jealous.

21
00:01:11,317 --> 00:01:13,019
Now that you've had two sons,

22
00:01:13,044 --> 00:01:14,982
there's really nothing left to envy.

23
00:01:15,119 --> 00:01:17,507
My husband's a bit disappointed.
He wanted a daughter.

24
00:01:18,012 --> 00:01:19,045
Me too, honestly.

25
00:01:19,070 --> 00:01:21,892
But what can we do? We've got two boys.

26
00:01:24,342 --> 00:01:25,741
You're going abroad
for a performance, right?

27
00:01:26,697 --> 00:01:28,608
Na Se Ri, you've really made it now.

28
00:01:28,633 --> 00:01:30,502
I'm the one who's jealous.

29
00:01:30,527 --> 00:01:33,421
- How did you know? You saw the article?
- My husband told me.

30
00:01:33,684 --> 00:01:35,572
When would I have time to read articles?

31
00:01:35,650 --> 00:01:37,616
I'm a full-on housewife now.

32
00:01:44,223 --> 00:01:45,268
Here.

33
00:01:45,963 --> 00:01:47,332
Thank you.

34
00:01:49,678 --> 00:01:51,285
Here you go.

35
00:02:03,302 --> 00:02:05,415
(3 years later)

36
00:02:13,724 --> 00:02:15,163
Yeong Ju.

37
00:02:15,478 --> 00:02:16,750
Hey, Na Se Ri.

38
00:02:17,250 --> 00:02:18,433
Cha Min Ki.

39
00:02:18,490 --> 00:02:21,544
How could you?
How could you do this to me?

40
00:02:21,703 --> 00:02:23,377
Seung Woo is only three years old!

41
00:02:23,402 --> 00:02:25,390
What am I supposed to do now?

42
00:02:25,415 --> 00:02:29,103
Yeong Ju, I'm sorry.

43
00:02:29,128 --> 00:02:31,203
"Sorry?"

44
00:02:31,384 --> 00:02:32,651
You bitch!

45
00:02:32,691 --> 00:02:35,491
I treated you better than my own sister.

46
00:02:35,516 --> 00:02:37,919
How could you stab me
in the back like this?

47
00:02:37,944 --> 00:02:40,419
How could you do this to me?

48
00:02:43,632 --> 00:02:46,410
She just gave birth. You can't do this.

49
00:02:46,769 --> 00:02:50,183
- "She just gave birth?"
- Yeong Ju.

50
00:02:50,372 --> 00:02:54,359
Min Ki said he'd give you everything.
Please, just agree to the divorce.

51
00:02:54,971 --> 00:02:56,118
Yeong Ju.

52
00:02:58,739 --> 00:02:59,996
No Yeong Ju.

53
00:03:01,232 --> 00:03:02,660
Do you know my name?

54
00:03:02,903 --> 00:03:06,188
That's right. I'm No Yeong Ju.

55
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:07,944
Don't forget it.

56
00:03:08,158 --> 00:03:10,499
I will never let you erase my name
from your records.

57
00:03:14,664 --> 00:03:16,471
Try living in the shadows like this
for the rest of your life.

58
00:03:16,764 --> 00:03:18,517
Let's see if you can ever work
under your own name.

59
00:03:19,197 --> 00:03:20,750
Yeong Ju.

60
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:23,650
Your daughter won't be able to face
the world either.

61
00:03:24,264 --> 00:03:25,984
I'll make sure the world
throws stones at her.

62
00:03:26,270 --> 00:03:28,510
What a parent's affair does to a child,

63
00:03:29,234 --> 00:03:32,384
I'll make sure she feels it
for the rest of her life.

64
00:03:32,843 --> 00:03:37,075
Min Ki, Yeong Ju, I'm sorry.

65
00:03:37,586 --> 00:03:39,964
I'm sorry, Yeong Ju. Please forgive me.

66
00:03:41,577 --> 00:03:45,477
When your daughter reaches my age,
she'll go through what I went through.

67
00:03:46,167 --> 00:03:47,349
I'll make sure of it.

68
00:03:48,644 --> 00:03:50,801
Yeong Ju, how could you say...

69
00:03:51,064 --> 00:03:53,999
How can you say that to a newborn baby?

70
00:03:54,024 --> 00:03:56,040
What did Ji Ni ever do wrong?

71
00:03:56,064 --> 00:03:57,567
Her crime is having you as a mother...

72
00:03:57,624 --> 00:03:59,511
and him as a father!

73
00:04:00,363 --> 00:04:02,158
What did my children ever do wrong...

74
00:04:02,182 --> 00:04:04,450
to deserve becoming
a single-parent family overnight?

75
00:04:04,695 --> 00:04:06,735
Is this my fault?
Did I do something wrong?

76
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:08,472
I'll take responsibility for the kids.

77
00:04:08,655 --> 00:04:10,500
- Just give me a divorce.
- "Responsibility?"

78
00:04:10,723 --> 00:04:13,486
After wrecking everything,
how are you going to take responsibility?

79
00:04:13,524 --> 00:04:17,537
Yeong Ju, I'll raise Seung Hyun
and Seung Woo well.

80
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,764
Please, Yeong Ju.

81
00:04:21,784 --> 00:04:24,814
We just fell in love.

82
00:04:25,442 --> 00:04:27,725
We weren't supposed to, but we did.

83
00:04:28,081 --> 00:04:29,258
"Love?"

84
00:04:30,498 --> 00:04:31,774
"Love?"

85
00:04:33,970 --> 00:04:35,894
What a load of bullshit.

86
00:04:36,731 --> 00:04:38,785
Yeong Ju, wait.

87
00:04:38,981 --> 00:04:41,274
Talk to me. This is all my fault.

88
00:04:42,184 --> 00:04:43,771
Don't take another step.

89
00:04:44,464 --> 00:04:46,365
I'd bury the three of you
alive right here,

90
00:04:46,389 --> 00:04:48,314
but I'm holding back
because the law won't allow it.

91
00:04:49,330 --> 00:04:50,538
And...

92
00:04:51,432 --> 00:04:52,611
that child...

93
00:04:53,261 --> 00:04:54,789
Don't you dare register her
under my son's name.

94
00:04:54,930 --> 00:04:56,741
She's Min Ki's daughter too!

95
00:04:56,784 --> 00:04:58,632
What right do you have to stop that?

96
00:04:58,657 --> 00:05:00,206
Go ahead, then.

97
00:05:01,004 --> 00:05:03,057
See what kind of world unfolds.

98
00:05:03,191 --> 00:05:04,773
Let's watch how a rising young cellist...

99
00:05:05,083 --> 00:05:07,781
gets completely destroyed...

100
00:05:08,942 --> 00:05:10,195
and goes up in flames.

101
00:05:12,372 --> 00:05:13,481
Yeong Ju.

102
00:05:18,842 --> 00:05:19,931
Se Ri.

103
00:05:59,504 --> 00:06:03,050
I couldn't shake the feeling
that my life had started all wrong.

104
00:06:03,324 --> 00:06:07,085
Only painting kept me breathing.

105
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:28,743
We must smell awful in this heat.
Hope we don't run into anyone.

106
00:06:28,767 --> 00:06:31,856
Right. I'm so glad masks are normal now.

107
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:34,253
- Right. Let's go!
- Let's go!

108
00:06:39,263 --> 00:06:41,535
Wait!

109
00:06:46,543 --> 00:06:47,903
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

110
00:06:47,928 --> 00:06:49,490
The doors are closing.

111
00:06:53,670 --> 00:06:55,302
What?

112
00:06:55,801 --> 00:06:57,586
Let's take the stairs!

113
00:07:01,917 --> 00:07:04,414
Right. Keep working hard, everyone.

114
00:07:05,237 --> 00:07:06,957
I'm so glad I'm not competing.

115
00:07:10,190 --> 00:07:12,071
Seriously?

116
00:07:18,017 --> 00:07:19,212
Yes, Mother!

117
00:07:19,334 --> 00:07:22,012
Yes. I'm at his company now.

118
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:26,262
He said he had a lot of work,
so I came to bring him lunch.

119
00:07:27,624 --> 00:07:29,197
Of course.

120
00:07:29,249 --> 00:07:32,928
I'm training to become
the perfect supportive wife.

121
00:07:32,953 --> 00:07:34,655
Okay.

122
00:07:34,679 --> 00:07:35,679
Goodbye.

123
00:07:39,610 --> 00:07:41,512
This is so annoying.

124
00:07:41,798 --> 00:07:44,298
She's about to transfer ownership,
but still acts like the boss.

125
00:07:53,910 --> 00:07:55,518
- I'm going to the restroom.
- Okay.

126
00:08:05,964 --> 00:08:07,156
Look who it is.

127
00:08:14,843 --> 00:08:17,816
My goodness. What a nice surprise.

128
00:08:17,919 --> 00:08:19,149
Na Ji Ni?

129
00:08:19,926 --> 00:08:21,078
What brings you here?

130
00:08:21,655 --> 00:08:23,935
The competition?

131
00:08:25,503 --> 00:08:28,000
Looks like you're still good at painting.

132
00:08:29,382 --> 00:08:30,382
Yes.

133
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:33,900
- It's been a while.
- "Been a while?"

134
00:08:34,663 --> 00:08:36,633
Who said you could talk to me
like we're equals?

135
00:08:36,784 --> 00:08:38,855
You had it easy while I was abroad, right?

136
00:08:39,016 --> 00:08:41,458
A cockroach like you
got to crawl around freely.

137
00:08:42,777 --> 00:08:43,797
What's wrong, Do Hee?

138
00:08:43,822 --> 00:08:46,366
I had to leave the country...

139
00:08:46,626 --> 00:08:48,783
because of brats
born from affairs like you.

140
00:08:48,910 --> 00:08:51,757
People like me,
born from a legitimate relationship...

141
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:54,988
and deserving of support,
are busy enough competing.

142
00:08:55,092 --> 00:08:58,601
Then someone filthy like you comes along,

143
00:08:58,663 --> 00:09:00,659
and you wonder why I'm so annoyed?

144
00:09:01,394 --> 00:09:02,555
I heard you went to Hanguk University.

145
00:09:02,804 --> 00:09:05,459
- You little...
- How could you say that?

146
00:09:06,419 --> 00:09:07,656
Everyone is equal.

147
00:09:07,824 --> 00:09:09,356
Equal?

148
00:09:13,703 --> 00:09:16,314
Look at you, all grown up.

149
00:09:18,091 --> 00:09:19,541
Looks like you need a lesson.

150
00:09:19,565 --> 00:09:20,825
Don't do this.

151
00:09:21,397 --> 00:09:22,678
I won't let you do this anymore.

152
00:09:22,737 --> 00:09:24,775
You're shaking,
and you say you won't take it?

153
00:09:25,284 --> 00:09:26,887
You're scared of me.

154
00:09:27,524 --> 00:09:29,109
You're trembling right now.

155
00:09:33,737 --> 00:09:34,737
Ji Ni.

156
00:09:36,072 --> 00:09:37,223
What are you doing there?

157
00:09:37,990 --> 00:09:38,990
Who is that?

158
00:09:41,151 --> 00:09:43,314
- Jeon Jung A?
- Do Do Hee?

159
00:09:43,890 --> 00:09:46,047
I heard you studied abroad.
So you're back?

160
00:09:46,128 --> 00:09:47,238
Obviously.

161
00:09:47,678 --> 00:09:49,981
You got prettier.
Which clinic did you go to?

162
00:09:50,036 --> 00:09:51,887
Excuse me? I was always pretty.

163
00:09:52,266 --> 00:09:54,532
I'm joking. Don't be so serious.

164
00:09:54,954 --> 00:09:57,621
- Did you submit your work?
- Yes. You too?

165
00:09:57,777 --> 00:10:00,532
Are you crazy?
Why would I enter this lame contest?

166
00:10:01,571 --> 00:10:03,379
My homecoming solo exhibition
is coming up soon.

167
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:05,585
The director here is my boyfriend.

168
00:10:05,873 --> 00:10:07,454
My dream is to be
the perfect wife and mother.

169
00:10:07,522 --> 00:10:10,521
You? Standards must have really dropped.

170
00:10:10,523 --> 00:10:13,010
Wait. I need the restroom too.

171
00:10:13,199 --> 00:10:14,721
Okay. Hurry back.

172
00:10:15,419 --> 00:10:17,200
Why do you hang out with her?

173
00:10:17,352 --> 00:10:19,467
What's wrong with Ji Ni?
She's better than you.

174
00:10:19,972 --> 00:10:23,296
- Look at that attitude.
- You're the one with the attitude.

175
00:10:23,298 --> 00:10:25,058
You little brat.

176
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:30,064
Seriously. Stop it!

177
00:10:32,961 --> 00:10:34,159
You psycho.

178
00:10:35,396 --> 00:10:39,088
- I want to free myself from this curse.
- Just wait.

179
00:10:42,131 --> 00:10:44,249
I did nothing wrong.

180
00:10:53,025 --> 00:10:56,074
Who did you run into?
You should've gone home.

181
00:10:56,076 --> 00:10:57,340
No.

182
00:10:58,001 --> 00:11:00,746
I came to get you lunch.
I couldn't just leave.

183
00:11:01,668 --> 00:11:02,764
Okay.

184
00:11:08,489 --> 00:11:09,662
Are you really okay?

185
00:11:13,230 --> 00:11:14,298
Who was it?

186
00:11:16,045 --> 00:11:17,180
Tell me.

187
00:11:21,683 --> 00:11:23,968
I told you when we were in England.

188
00:11:24,326 --> 00:11:26,779
I was bullied in middle school.

189
00:11:26,831 --> 00:11:28,352
You met that bully?

190
00:11:30,165 --> 00:11:31,358
Na Ji Ni.

191
00:11:31,728 --> 00:11:33,957
I think she came
to enter the competition today.

192
00:11:34,361 --> 00:11:37,173
- After almost ten years.
- You must've been shocked.

193
00:11:37,259 --> 00:11:41,066
Honestly, this is hard for me to say,

194
00:11:41,946 --> 00:11:44,260
but I'm saying it for everyone's sake.

195
00:11:44,262 --> 00:11:46,384
Don't think I'm trying to smear her.

196
00:11:46,386 --> 00:11:48,958
I don't like interfering in anyone's life.

197
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:50,956
- You know that, right?
- I know.

198
00:11:57,113 --> 00:12:00,965
She should be barred from the art world.

199
00:12:02,177 --> 00:12:04,377
Even if her work is good,
you can't let it through.

200
00:12:05,496 --> 00:12:09,250
I was so shaken up,
I still can't calm down.

201
00:12:13,164 --> 00:12:16,269
It's okay.

202
00:12:18,233 --> 00:12:22,209
She always came in second to me
in middle school.

203
00:12:22,566 --> 00:12:23,967
I guess she never got over it.

204
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,666
Her mom's a famous cellist,

205
00:12:27,794 --> 00:12:29,666
and she couldn't stand
her daughter coming in second.

206
00:12:30,182 --> 00:12:32,907
- Her mom beat her all the time.
- So she took it out on you?

207
00:12:35,855 --> 00:12:38,349
I couldn't tell you everything
back in England,

208
00:12:39,532 --> 00:12:42,959
but when I saw her today,

209
00:12:44,636 --> 00:12:47,259
it brought back memories
of being locked in the bathroom.

210
00:12:49,373 --> 00:12:52,660
You're going to reject her painting,
right, Ji Hu?

211
00:12:57,095 --> 00:13:01,057
- I'll bring it up at the meeting.
- What? I was the victim!

212
00:13:01,139 --> 00:13:03,663
Ji Hu, don't you believe me?

213
00:13:05,706 --> 00:13:07,154
You must've had such a hard time.

214
00:13:09,839 --> 00:13:11,547
Even after ten years.

215
00:13:15,731 --> 00:13:17,588
That's what school bullying does.

216
00:13:18,647 --> 00:13:20,662
It's really terrifying.

217
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:38,306
Then I guess I'm out.
I pulled an all-nighter for nothing.

218
00:13:38,332 --> 00:13:41,457
Hey, do you think it would matter
if Do Hee's boyfriend were in charge?

219
00:13:41,501 --> 00:13:45,875
- It doesn't work like that in Korea.
- I told you, I'm just unlucky.

220
00:13:46,419 --> 00:13:48,714
It's okay. I'll just try somewhere else.

221
00:13:48,716 --> 00:13:51,862
Why jump that far ahead?
We only just submitted ours.

222
00:13:53,334 --> 00:13:55,301
Excuse me, could we get a soda, please?

223
00:13:55,587 --> 00:13:59,872
- What soda? Bring us soju.
- Okay.

224
00:13:59,874 --> 00:14:03,481
Are you sure?
You said you'd pass out if you drank.

225
00:14:03,483 --> 00:14:04,862
Come on. It'll be fine.

226
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:12,730
- Here.
- Thank you.

227
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:20,877
Good job, Jung A.

228
00:14:21,688 --> 00:14:25,725
- Good luck.
- Hey, you need it too.

229
00:14:25,727 --> 00:14:28,275
- Your talent isn't going anywhere.
- I guess so, right?

230
00:14:28,811 --> 00:14:31,342
If not good luck,
I hope I can at least avoid bad luck.

231
00:14:31,344 --> 00:14:32,905
I'm sure you will.

232
00:14:41,885 --> 00:14:43,338
It's your dad.

233
00:14:43,806 --> 00:14:45,766
Was your phone off?

234
00:14:46,954 --> 00:14:50,228
Yes, Dad. Sure.

235
00:14:50,230 --> 00:14:52,070
We submitted just in time,

236
00:14:52,071 --> 00:14:53,963
and now we're just having
spicy rice cakes and soju...

237
00:14:55,067 --> 00:14:56,166
What?

238
00:14:57,658 --> 00:15:00,376
- Okay.
- What's going on?

239
00:15:28,504 --> 00:15:31,565
I kept quiet so I wouldn't distract you
from your deadline.

240
00:15:33,008 --> 00:15:35,172
What happened?

241
00:15:36,059 --> 00:15:38,250
It's because of me.

242
00:15:39,476 --> 00:15:42,416
- Why?
- Today is your grandfather's memorial.

243
00:15:42,418 --> 00:15:44,939
Grandfather?
The one who lived in Seo Chon?

244
00:15:44,941 --> 00:15:47,786
I kept dreaming about him,

245
00:15:47,933 --> 00:15:50,440
so I said I was going back
to the family home for the memorial.

246
00:15:50,442 --> 00:15:51,447
"The family home?"

247
00:15:51,449 --> 00:15:54,123
I can't keep avoiding
my father's memorial forever.

248
00:15:54,125 --> 00:15:55,551
I'm his son, after all.

249
00:15:57,228 --> 00:15:59,157
If that's the family home,
then what is this place?

250
00:15:59,962 --> 00:16:05,968
Ji Ni, that's not what's important.
It's just my childhood home.

251
00:16:06,461 --> 00:16:09,554
And that's exactly why Mom is so upset.

252
00:16:09,556 --> 00:16:13,235
Even though we live like this,
you always called here your home.

253
00:16:13,237 --> 00:16:14,991
That's right. This is my home.

254
00:16:14,993 --> 00:16:18,163
My family is just you and your mom.

255
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:20,439
But Dad, you're not making any sense.

256
00:16:20,441 --> 00:16:22,569
Please don't keep going back and forth
like that.

257
00:16:23,107 --> 00:16:26,576
The reason I never felt deprived
living as Na Ji Ni...

258
00:16:26,832 --> 00:16:29,471
was because you were always here with us.

259
00:16:29,621 --> 00:16:31,988
But now you're suddenly saying
you're going back to your family home.

260
00:16:32,175 --> 00:16:35,380
And it's not even
while Grandfather is alive.

261
00:16:35,676 --> 00:16:37,576
No wonder mom is confused.

262
00:16:38,453 --> 00:16:40,397
Please try to understand me.

263
00:16:40,487 --> 00:16:42,762
I've been having
a really hard time lately.

264
00:16:44,364 --> 00:16:46,060
Mom asks me to understand her.

265
00:16:46,679 --> 00:16:48,465
Dad asks me to understand him.

266
00:16:49,762 --> 00:16:50,924
Then,

267
00:16:52,101 --> 00:16:54,187
who am I supposed to ask to understand me?

268
00:16:54,254 --> 00:16:57,298
Why are you acting like this too?
You were always on my side.

269
00:17:00,959 --> 00:17:03,134
I'll ask the housekeeper
to clear this away.

270
00:17:03,885 --> 00:17:05,376
Go ahead and visit him.

271
00:17:16,048 --> 00:17:17,349
Leave.

272
00:17:18,128 --> 00:17:19,586
Leave!

273
00:17:20,338 --> 00:17:22,859
Move. This is my house.
Why can't I come in?

274
00:17:22,861 --> 00:17:25,320
How is this your house?

275
00:17:25,584 --> 00:17:27,646
You abandoned this house.

276
00:17:29,622 --> 00:17:30,760
I said leave.

277
00:17:32,691 --> 00:17:34,886
Leave? You little punk.

278
00:17:34,888 --> 00:17:37,405
It's my father's memorial.
Who are you to stop me?

279
00:17:37,407 --> 00:17:39,670
- You disrespectful brat.
- "My father?"

280
00:17:41,101 --> 00:17:42,173
Who are you talking about?

281
00:17:42,804 --> 00:17:46,065
"My son is dead."
Do I need to remind you of his last words?

282
00:17:47,244 --> 00:17:49,187
I put up with all
the horrible things you did...

283
00:17:49,547 --> 00:17:51,869
because I thought you were dead.

284
00:17:52,380 --> 00:17:54,008
I don't have a father.

285
00:17:54,024 --> 00:17:57,440
My dad is dead.

286
00:17:57,442 --> 00:17:59,454
You little punk.

287
00:17:59,661 --> 00:18:01,066
Talk to me.

288
00:18:02,740 --> 00:18:04,208
What is there to talk about?

289
00:18:04,404 --> 00:18:07,096
- You have something to discuss with him?
- Seung Woo, stop.

290
00:18:07,098 --> 00:18:09,071
- Stop what?
- Seung Woo!

291
00:18:45,912 --> 00:18:47,704
I have to greet him...

292
00:18:51,238 --> 00:18:53,974
Go ahead. Greet him.

293
00:18:54,599 --> 00:18:56,058
He's O Reum's grandfather.

294
00:18:56,962 --> 00:19:01,873
- Hello. I'm Dang Ngoc Mai.
- Nice to meet you.

295
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:05,943
- Sorry I couldn't attend your wedding.
- Exactly.

296
00:19:12,053 --> 00:19:15,279
This is Cha O Reum.

297
00:19:19,279 --> 00:19:20,777
My boy.

298
00:19:22,014 --> 00:19:25,074
I must be getting old.
Kids are so adorable.

299
00:19:25,821 --> 00:19:26,956
Thank you.

300
00:19:27,491 --> 00:19:29,564
I'll give you a nice gift later.

301
00:19:29,565 --> 00:19:34,297
Looking at O Reum now,
I think he looks a lot like you.

302
00:19:34,299 --> 00:19:35,464
Mai.

303
00:19:36,845 --> 00:19:41,057
You two talk. O Reum, let's go.

304
00:19:54,824 --> 00:19:56,355
I just...

305
00:19:57,233 --> 00:20:01,288
I thought I should at least come
on my father's memorial day now.

306
00:20:01,475 --> 00:20:03,855
- Why?
- How can you even ask that?

307
00:20:04,183 --> 00:20:07,122
It didn't feel right
leaving it all to you.

308
00:20:08,933 --> 00:20:10,455
I'm sorry, it's taken me this long.

309
00:20:10,641 --> 00:20:12,308
Yeah, it really has.

310
00:20:13,166 --> 00:20:14,374
Please leave.

311
00:20:14,850 --> 00:20:16,475
He's not alive anymore.
What's the point now?

312
00:20:18,516 --> 00:20:20,100
Did Se Ri just let you come here
without a fuss?

313
00:20:23,266 --> 00:20:25,641
Don't come back now
and make things complicated.

314
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:28,765
- Just keep it in your heart, like before.
- Yeong Ju.

315
00:20:28,766 --> 00:20:31,350
More than greeting your dead father,

316
00:20:31,725 --> 00:20:34,933
it matters more not to hurt my son
who's still alive.

317
00:20:35,308 --> 00:20:37,016
Your situation, your change,

318
00:20:37,558 --> 00:20:39,161
I have no intention
of accepting any of it.

319
00:20:45,683 --> 00:20:47,183
You still have this?

320
00:20:52,516 --> 00:20:53,851
You completely killed me off.

321
00:20:54,641 --> 00:20:55,951
No wonder I...

322
00:20:59,281 --> 00:21:00,934
You'll get what you wished for.

323
00:21:04,433 --> 00:21:05,725
Get out. Now!

324
00:21:06,766 --> 00:21:08,141
What's wrong with that kid?

325
00:21:18,641 --> 00:21:20,884
What's with Seung Woo's temper?

326
00:21:21,975 --> 00:21:24,349
Unlike me, he really liked you.

327
00:21:24,350 --> 00:21:25,401
And you?

328
00:21:25,740 --> 00:21:28,651
I'm just... whatever.

329
00:21:30,266 --> 00:21:31,642
You're the scarier one.

330
00:21:38,641 --> 00:21:39,992
Go tell Seung Woo this,

331
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:42,076
no matter what, he's still my son.

332
00:21:42,558 --> 00:21:44,517
When a man falls in love,

333
00:21:44,641 --> 00:21:47,351
no one can control him.

334
00:21:47,933 --> 00:21:49,308
Love is like a car accident.

335
00:21:49,350 --> 00:21:51,057
You think you'll be safe your whole life?

336
00:21:51,058 --> 00:21:52,266
Don't say things like that.

337
00:21:52,850 --> 00:21:54,307
We won't live like you.

338
00:21:54,308 --> 00:21:55,725
Don't get cocky.

339
00:21:55,808 --> 00:21:57,763
You studied with my money.

340
00:22:10,141 --> 00:22:11,461
That ungrateful brat...

341
00:22:12,683 --> 00:22:14,161
Seriously.

342
00:22:46,131 --> 00:22:48,131
I haven't even properly apologized yet.

343
00:22:49,725 --> 00:22:53,222
I couldn't even act like a father
at Seung Hyun's wedding.

344
00:22:55,141 --> 00:22:56,855
I still have so much left to do.

345
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,808
Father.

346
00:23:02,933 --> 00:23:04,745
Am I really going to die?

347
00:23:07,683 --> 00:23:08,891
Mom.

348
00:23:10,074 --> 00:23:11,574
What should I do now?

349
00:23:46,225 --> 00:23:47,516
Why are you here already?

350
00:23:48,391 --> 00:23:49,600
They kicked me out.

351
00:23:54,016 --> 00:23:55,225
That's too bad.

352
00:24:00,266 --> 00:24:02,130
I made a fool of myself.

353
00:24:24,807 --> 00:24:27,509
I can't keep avoiding
my father's memorial forever.

354
00:24:28,141 --> 00:24:29,542
I'm his son, after all.

355
00:24:45,183 --> 00:24:46,390
This is nice.

356
00:24:46,391 --> 00:24:48,262
It may not hold 30,
but around 20 should fit.

357
00:24:48,263 --> 00:24:50,720
They can dine comfortably
and hold meetings here.

358
00:24:51,086 --> 00:24:52,933
Great. It's spacious enough.

359
00:24:53,391 --> 00:24:56,480
The CEO said even private rooms
at restaurants make him uncomfortable.

360
00:24:57,058 --> 00:24:58,600
There are no secrets in this world.

361
00:24:58,683 --> 00:25:00,388
Right. Please feel free to use this place.

362
00:25:00,766 --> 00:25:02,455
General Im, that's impressive.

363
00:25:02,641 --> 00:25:05,933
Please. It's the least I can do
after all you've done for me.

364
00:25:06,891 --> 00:25:10,334
Why did you retire, then?
You could've made it to the top.

365
00:25:10,850 --> 00:25:12,974
I told you I was sick of the sea.

366
00:25:12,975 --> 00:25:14,307
The Navy uniform drew me in,

367
00:25:14,308 --> 00:25:16,515
but I left to live
with my feet on the ground.

368
00:25:16,516 --> 00:25:17,808
Maybe that's true,

369
00:25:18,308 --> 00:25:20,695
but I feel like there's another reason.

370
00:25:21,308 --> 00:25:23,113
There isn't.

371
00:25:23,225 --> 00:25:26,808
Then I'll prepare for this weekend's
party executive meeting.

372
00:25:26,850 --> 00:25:29,265
Thank you. We'll owe you one.

373
00:25:29,266 --> 00:25:30,933
I'll be sure to tell the CEO.

374
00:25:30,975 --> 00:25:32,975
Great, I'll see you off here.

375
00:25:36,461 --> 00:25:37,474
- Follow him.
- Yes, sir.

376
00:25:37,488 --> 00:25:39,183
Confirm who will handle the details.

377
00:25:39,225 --> 00:25:40,433
Yes, sir.

378
00:25:48,016 --> 00:25:49,225
You'd better come.

379
00:25:49,808 --> 00:25:52,227
If you don't, I don't know what I'll do.

380
00:25:52,725 --> 00:25:55,493
I'm crazy, so don't ignore me.
Be there on time.

381
00:26:04,225 --> 00:26:07,085
Are you seriously doing this?

382
00:26:07,266 --> 00:26:09,185
What happened in Seo Chon?

383
00:26:09,985 --> 00:26:11,468
I'll explain. Just wait.

384
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:17,393
- Is someone else coming?
- Yes.

385
00:26:34,433 --> 00:26:36,197
What is going on?

386
00:26:38,183 --> 00:26:39,391
You two.

387
00:26:40,141 --> 00:26:41,408
You!

388
00:26:49,229 --> 00:26:50,229
(Medical Report)

389
00:26:52,058 --> 00:26:53,829
They say I'm going to die soon.

390
00:26:54,641 --> 00:26:55,850
Pancreatic cancer.

391
00:26:56,249 --> 00:26:57,839
And it's in a very bad spot.

392
00:27:06,475 --> 00:27:07,966
Dr. Hwang diagnosed me.

393
00:27:08,558 --> 00:27:10,000
It's because of you two.

394
00:27:10,391 --> 00:27:12,140
You even put up a mourning ribbon...

395
00:27:12,141 --> 00:27:13,765
and prayed for me to die.

396
00:27:13,766 --> 00:27:15,391
You've been stuck in my throat...

397
00:27:15,433 --> 00:27:16,724
like a piece of steel,

398
00:27:16,725 --> 00:27:18,475
not going down, not bursting,

399
00:27:18,516 --> 00:27:19,766
but tormenting me my whole life.

400
00:27:19,767 --> 00:27:22,170
Yeong Ju, you actually put up
a mourning ribbon?

401
00:27:22,958 --> 00:27:23,766
Unbelievable.

402
00:27:23,766 --> 00:27:25,904
Don't interrupt.
You're not innocent either.

403
00:27:25,975 --> 00:27:28,683
You picked at me morning and night...

404
00:27:28,975 --> 00:27:31,479
until you destroyed me.

405
00:27:31,983 --> 00:27:34,435
You two have eaten away at me inside.

406
00:27:34,850 --> 00:27:36,827
I'm dying without even getting surgery.

407
00:27:37,350 --> 00:27:39,141
I'm only 60.

408
00:27:41,100 --> 00:27:42,506
Honey.

409
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:44,308
Is this true?

410
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:47,210
Give me ten years of your life.

411
00:27:48,433 --> 00:27:49,641
What?

412
00:27:49,891 --> 00:27:51,933
I said give me ten years of your life.

413
00:27:52,449 --> 00:27:53,991
After making me suffer like this,

414
00:27:54,016 --> 00:27:55,880
you two have to save me.

415
00:27:56,832 --> 00:28:00,562
Save me!

416
00:28:23,516 --> 00:28:26,725
(Family Register)

417
00:28:26,850 --> 00:28:29,183
You women, am I really that terrible?

418
00:28:29,225 --> 00:28:30,390
I don't want to save you.

419
00:28:30,391 --> 00:28:32,974
Even facing death,
please reflect on what you've done.

420
00:28:32,975 --> 00:28:36,145
Just think about us. You, me, and Ji Ni.

421
00:28:36,147 --> 00:28:37,975
To me, you and Mom
were my father.

422
00:28:38,016 --> 00:28:40,266
Let him die with all that resentment
in his heart.

423
00:28:40,347 --> 00:28:42,225
You're still my enemy. Until the very end.

424
00:28:42,391 --> 00:28:43,975
I'll have my revenge.

425
00:28:44,016 --> 00:28:47,276
I'll make you pay for all the tears
and the pain I've suffered.

426
00:28:50,928 --> 00:28:52,928
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
